The paper deals with path routing over road networks, which involves data management and retrieval, making it relevant to the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes effective pruning methods and indexing mechanisms, which are common techniques in data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves extensive experiments to demonstrate the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed approaches, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
